<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2010 GMT, Wednesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak is leaving Camp
David in the United States and the summit with the Palestinians
there for reaching a peace deal seemed to fail, Barak's One Israel
coalition whip Ophir Pines-Paz confirmed here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He said he did not believe Barak's leaving is a negotiation
maneuver, adding that according to his sources, the American
sponsors shared with Barak the judgement that the Palestinians
adopted too tough stands in the talks. (Israel-Barak-Return)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BEIRUT -- Syrian President Bashar al-Assad will pay an official
visit to Lebanon in the next few weeks as part of an Arab tour that
is expected to take him to Saudi Arabia, Jordan, Egypt, Bahrain and
other countries, An Nahar newspaper reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The tour is aimed at thanking the leaders of those countries for
the sympathy they expressed on the death of late Syrian President
Hafez al-Assad, who passed away on June 10. (Lebanon-Syria-Visit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran's anti-narcotics agents have managed to seize
some 1.5 tons of morphine in Tehran and the northwestern city of
Mianeh in the past few days, a high-ranking security officer said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
One ton of the confiscated drugs had been concealed in a gas
tanker and were detected by sniffer dogs in Mianeh," Tehran's
security forces Brigadier General Mohsen Ansari said.
</P>
<P>
He added that during the operation, six traffickers were
arrested who confessed to concealing another 500 kilograms of
morphine in eastern Tehran for transit to Turkey. (Iran-Morphine)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iranian Foreign Ministry spokesman Hamid Reza Asefi on
Wednesday condemned Iraq for the recent attacks on the country by
the Iraq-based Iranian opposition group Mujaheddin Khalq
Organization (MKO).
</P>
<P>
Iran holds the Iraqi government responsible for the terrorist
acts committed by the MKO in Iran, Asefi was quoted by the Islamic
Republic News Agency as saying. (Iran-Iraq-MKO)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran's supreme leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei on
Wednesday appointed Rear Admiral Ali Akbar Ahmadian new chief of
the Joint Staff Headquarters of the elite Islamic Revolution Guards
Corps (IRGC).
</P>
<P>
Ahmadian was originally navy commander of the IRGC, but the
place has now been taken by Morteza Safavi, who is also promoted
from commodore to the rank of rear admiral, according to another
order issued by the supreme leader, the Islamic Republic News
Agency reported. (Iran-Leader-Appointments) 
</P>
</TEXT>
