<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Russian Prime Minister Mikhail
Kasyanov and his Ukrainian counterpart, Viktor Yushchenko, agreed
here Wednesday to speed up the settlement of the mutual debts of
the two countries.
</P>
<P>
After his meeting with Yushchenko, Kasyanov told reporters that
Moscow will honor its pledge to quickly address its debts to
Ukraine over the Black Sea fleet.
</P>
<P>
