represents a major step forward in EU-Croatia bilateral relations,
following the election of a new political leadership advocating
radical political and economic reform in the Balkan country.
</P>
<P>
This proposal is a great step forward in EU efforts to
stabilize the region, said EU commissioner for external relations
Chris Patten. "It is a tribute to the courageous steps taken by
the new Croatia government in the short time it has been in office,
" he said.
</P>
<P>
The new agreement with Croatia will be the second under the EU
Stabilization and Association Process, launched last year with the
aim of strengthening political and economic stability in the
Balkan region. Such an agreement is already under negotiation with
the former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia, the Commission said in
a statement.
