<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Romania Delegation Calls for Lifting U.N. Embargo on Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, July 19 (Xinhua) -- A Romanian delegation currently
visiting Iraq has sent a letter to the United Nations Secretary
General Kofi Annan calling for lifting the U.N. embargo on Iraq,
the official Iraqi News Agency (INA) reported on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The letter stressed that the decade-old U.N. embargo on Iraq
must be ended because it violates the U.N. Charter as well as
Iraq's sovereignty and territorial integrity.
</P>
<P>
If the embargo is to continue, it will kill more Iraqis because
of the acute shortage of food and medicine, the letter said.
</P>
<P>
Iraq said that as many as 1.3 million people, mostly children
and the elderly, have died as a direct result of the stringent
embargo imposed in 1990 following Iraq's invasion of neighboring
Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
Iraq has repeatedly accused the U.S. and Britain of putting on
hold contracts it signed with foreign countries to import food,
medicine and other humanitarian supplies within the framework of
the U.N. oil-for-food program.
</P>
<P>
The U.N. humanitarian program, which allows Iraq to export oil
in return for humanitarian goods, is an exemption to the sweeping
and crippling U.N. sanctions still in force.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian delegation came here to attend the 32nd anniversary
of the Iraqi July revolution, through which the Arab Baath
Socialist Party came to power in 1968 and has ruled Iraq since
then. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
