<HEADLINE> Fist Fight Breaks out Aboard Turkish Airlines Flight to Cairo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, July 19 (Xinhua) -- A fist fight broke out aboard a
Turkish Airlines flight to Cairo on Wednesday when a German
passenger tried to stop a Turkish passenger from making a mobile
telephone call, airport officials said.
</P>
<P>
A number of passengers asked the Turk, Abideen Farul, not to
make the call after the cabin crew announced that using cell phones
could affect the navigation of the plane, which was preparing to
descend into Cairo International Airport, Egypt's Middle East News
Agency quoted the officials as saying.
</P>
<P>
But Farul ignored them, and then came to blows with a German
passenger of Egyptian origin, Ahmed Hashem, who tried to force him
to end the call.
</P>
<P>
Police at Cairo airport booked and warned the two passengers who
were bruised after the skirmish.
</P>
<P>
It was the third incident aboard planes using Cairo airport in
less than a week.
</P>
<P>
Two Palestinians engaged in a drunken brawl on an Air Ukraine
flight from Kiev to Cairo on Sunday, forcing fellow passengers to
try to stop them and the pilot to radio authorities on the ground,
the officials said.
</P>
<P>
And on Friday a Saudi passenger who refused to wear his safety
belt was taken off a Saudi Arabian Airlines flight at the Cairo
airport after delaying take-off for an hour, they added. 
</P>
