<HEADLINE> Russia, US to Confer on Funding Arms Pullout From Georgia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Officials from Russia and the
United States will hold talks on U.S. financial assistance for the
withdrawal of Russia's military weaponry from Georgia, the
Interfax news agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A group of U.S. experts led by Special Adviser to the President
William Taylor arrived here Tuesday for the consultations,
Interfax said, quoting diplomatic sources.
</P>
<P>
Under an understanding reached by Russia and Georgia at the
summit of the Organization for Security and Cooperation in Russia
in Istanbul last year, Russia should cut its military hardware in
Georgia to the level set by the Conventional Forces in Europe(CFE)
by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
Officials from several Russian Foreign Ministry departments are
expected to attend.
</P>
<P>
"Technical details related to the transfer of funds from the
United States to be spent in financing the withdrawal of Russian
military hardware stationed on Georgian territory" will be
discussed at the consultations, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
"It is a question of allocating some 10 million U.S. dollars to
Moscow and Tbilisi, the bulk of which will be given to Russia,"
Interfax quoted the sources as saying. 
</P>
