<HEADLINE> High Street Sales In UK Show Improvement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 19 (Xinhua)-- Retail sales rose more than expected
in June, raising fears that UK economy was overheating.
</P>
<P>
The Office for National Statistics (ONS) said Wednesday that
retail sales last month grew by 0.7 percent - stronger than many
economists was expecting.
</P>
<P>
According to the office, for the three months to the end of
June, the volume of sales is up 0.3 percent more than in the
previous three months and 4.3 percent than in the same period a
year earlier.
</P>
<P>
Economic analysts in the City have been predicting sales growth
of just 0.1 percent on the month, compared to 0.5 percent in May.
</P>
<P>
They said that the data released by the ONS warns that the
slowdown seen earlier in the year might prove to be temporary or
at least not as marked as originally seemed to be the case.
</P>
