<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1530 GMT, July 19 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA -- Indonesian Navy Chief of Staff Adm.Achmad Sutjipto
Wednesday said he did not believe foreign warships would dare to
trespass on Indonesian waters to intervene in the Maluku conflict.
</P>
<P>
"It's not likely to happen. The risks would be too high. I
think no country would purposely provoke an incident at sea,"
Sutjipto told reporters in Surabaya, capital of East Java.
</P>
<P>
The Navy chief was commenting on reports that a United States
warship had recently been spotted sailing in the vicinity of Biak
in Irian Jaya province. (Indonesia-Foreign Warships)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- The Russian State Duma on Wednesday overwhelmingly
ratified the Treaty of Friendship, Neighborliness and Cooperation
with the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK).
</P>
<P>
The treaty cleared the lower house of parliament by a vote of
363-8 with one abstention. The required majority was 266 votes.
</P>
<P>
The ratification coincided with the visit to DPRK by Russian
President Vladimir Putin, who arrived in Pyongyang earlier
Wednesday on the first trip by a Russian head of state to the
north Asian nation. (Russia-DPRK-Friendship Treaty)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ANTWERP, Belgium -- The world diamond industry on Wednesday
announced their intent and measures to combat trading in conflict
diamonds that have been used to fund wars in Africa.
</P>
<P>
Some 350 diamond miners, dealers, cutters, polishers and
government representatives from around the world decided after
three days of conference to introduce new strict measures to close
off all legal loopholes through which conflict diamonds have been
entering the international market.
</P>
<P>
One of the new measures will be a certification system to
monitor rough diamonds from the mines where they are found all the
way to international trading centers. (Fight-Conflict Diamonds)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak is preparing to
walk out of the Middle East peace summit in Camp David without a
deal with the Palestinians, a senior Israeli source said on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Barak is preparing to return home at the soonest moment after
it became clear to him that the Palestinians are not a true
partner for peace," the source was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
He said Israel was warning the Palestinians "not to take
unilateral steps or inflame violence in the region."
</P>
<P>
But Barak's official spokesman Gadi Baltiansky refused to
comment on the report. "I cannot comment on this report," he said.
(Mideast-Barak) 
</P>
