<HEADLINE> Official Calls for Social Stability in Xinjiang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Chinese State Councilor Ismail
Ahmad said today that social stability in the Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region must be consolidated by accelerating economic
development.
</P>
<P>
Speaking in this capital of the region, he urged local
officials to adhere to President Jiang Zemin's instructions, and
take into consideration the people's fundamental interests.
</P>
<P>
When attending a tourism fair here, he said that Xinjiang has
opened a new chapter for tourism development, which will benefit
local economy.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that Xinjiang is located on the ancient Silk
Road, where there are numerous historical sites and relics that
can be used to attract visitors.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Xinjiang's landscape is among the most beautiful
in the country, he said.
</P>
<P>
The development of tourism can enhance the exchanges between
different ethnic groups, and thus consolidate their friendly
relations, he stressed. 
</P>
