<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Cases of bubonic plague carried
by marmots have been found in several provinces in Mongolia, but
no people have been reported infected with this disease so far, an
official at the country's infectious disease research center said
on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
