<HEADLINE> Freeway Built to World's Earliest Dam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, July 19 (Xinhua) -- An expressway connecting this
capital of southwest China's Sichuan Province with Dujiangyan City,
where the world's earliest water-conservation project --
Dujiangyan Weir -- locates, became operational today.
</P>
<P>
Now it takes only 20 minutes to cover the 59 km between the two
cities.
</P>
<P>
The expressway, which cost 1.043 billion yuan (about 125
million U.S. dollars), is 40.439 km long. It has six lanes.
</P>
<P>
The construction work lasted seven months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
