<HEADLINE> Flooded Railway Reopens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Most sections of the railway line
in southern Xinjiang have been repaired and reopened after days of
suspension due to floods.
</P>
<P>
The railway is the most important line in the Xinjiang Uygur
Autonomous Region. Floods caused by rainstorms damaged 20 sections
of the railway and forced six trains to stop midway.
</P>
<P>
The local railway bureau has mobilized more than 1,000 people
to repair the damage. By 16:00 pm today most of the damaged
sections had been restored.
</P>
<P>
Sources said that the railway line will be fully reopen by 12:
00 pm Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The flood was the second largest in the region since 1996.
</P>
</TEXT>
