<HEADLINE> China's First Social Insurance Info Network Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 19 (Xinhua) -- China's first provincial-level
social insurance information network became operational today in
south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong's old-age pension fund amounts to over 14 billion
yuan (about 1.68 billion US dollars), accounting for 20 percent of
the country's total. The information system can help improve the
efficiency of pension payments.
</P>
<P>
The network has pooled social insurance information from many
government branches including social security, civil
administration, public health, finance and public security.
</P>
<P>
You Ningfeng, vice-governor of Guangdong, urged the various
departments to make sure they update their data promptly.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government plans to computerize the social
security system by the year 2005. The province's coverage rate of
unemployment insurance is expected to reach 95 percent by the end
of this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
