<HEADLINE> Metallurgical Industrial Profits Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 19 (Xinhua) -- China's metallurgical industry
achieved a profit of 5.43 billion yuan in the first half of this
year, 4.2 billion yuan more than in the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Officials at the State Administration of the Metallurgical
Industry attributed the increase to the pick-up of domestic steel
prices.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the combined industrial output value of
the country's key iron and steel companies reached 104.7 billion
yuan in the six-month period, up 11.4 percent on a yearly basis.
Their sales income reached 155.8 billion yuan, up 18.9 percent.
</P>
<P>
From January to June, 15 more iron and steel giants started to
yield profits; at present, only 24.7 percent of the country's key
metallurgical enterprises remain loss-making.
</P>
<P>
China exported 5.66 million tons of steel and steel products in
the period, tripling the figure for the same 1999 period. A total
of 15 iron and steel enterprises reported exports of more than 100,
000 tons of products each.
</P>
<P>
And the country imported 8.61 million tons of steel and steel
products in the first half of this year, down 1.03 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
