<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EU's Aid to Lebanon in 1999 Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, July 19 (Xinhua) -- The assistance given by the European
Union (EU) to Lebanon in 1999 exceeded 228 million euros (200
million U.S. dollars), up 40 percent from the aid in 1998, An Nahar
Newspaper reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper quoted a report issued by the EU in Beirut as
saying that the total assistance provided by the EU to Lebanon
since 1977 when the EU established relations with Lebanon has
exceeded 1.8
billion euros (1.58 billion dollars), which accounts for 40 percent
of the total international aid to Lebanon during the period.
</P>
<P>
The report, which is the yearly account of the activities of the
EU in Lebanon, showed most of the assistance provided by the EU was
spent on reconstruction projects.
</P>
<P>
The EU recently formally notified Lebanon of its intention to
increase the pledged 120 million euros (105 million dollars) of aid
to more than 200 million euros (180 million U.S. dollars) for the
1996-2000 period.
</P>
<P>
The money will be used in projects dealing with reconstruction,
economic and social development, human right, environmental
protection and refugee assistance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
