<HEADLINE> 6 Identified as Arms Heist Masterminds in Malaysia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Six members of the Al Ma'unah
deviant group including its leader Mohamed Amin Mohd Razali have
been identified as the masterminds behind the arms heist at two
army camps in Gerik in Malaysia's northern state of Perak on July
2, police said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Besides Mohamed Amin, the others also include a Malaysian air
force serviceman Capt Jamaluddin Darus.
</P>
<P>
"We believe they play a key role in our investigations,"
Bernama news agency quoted police officer Hamzah Shamsuddin of the
Kuala Kangsar police station as telling reporters in Kuala Kangsar,
Perak, where the six are detained since July 6.
</P>
<P>
Hamzah said the six had given their cooperation to the
investigating team.
</P>
<P>
The six are among 27 who are allegedly involved in the arms
robbery on July 2 at the Sungai Rui army post and Territorial Army
's Battalion 304 camp and surrendered on July 6.
</P>
<P>
Twenty other members of the group are being held in the Perak
police headquarters in Ipoh and another is undergoing treatment in
Ipoh Hospital in the state.
</P>
<P>
Hamzah said: "Police are expediting the investigations as it is
of national interest and hope to complete the probe before August
1, the date the remand order expires." 
