<HEADLINE> China's Fund Market on Wednesday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 19 (Xinhua) -- China's securities investment fund
market continued yesterday's upward trend today. Among 27 funds,
25 rose, and two remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Fund Xinghua, which was the gainer today, surged four percent.
Two funds that kept unchanged were Fund Zhujiang and Fund Yulong,
according to Homeway, China's leading on-line financial and
securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
As for the 12 funds on the Shanghai Stock Exchange, totally 1.
941 billion fund units changed hangs, up 121 percent compared with
yesterday's 0.877 billion fund units. This showed that hot money
in the market had flowed into the new fund market, said Homeway.
</P>
<P>
The Shanghai Stock Exchange Fund Index created another new high
today, closing at 1061.63 points today, up 2.46 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
