<HEADLINE> Barak Leaving Camp David: Coalition Whip EDS: Updates with details </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak
is leaving Camp David and the summit with the Palestinians for
reaching a peace deal seemed to fail, Barak's One Israel coalition
whip Ophir Pines-Paz confirmed here a short while ago Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Unfortunately, that's all the information I have for the
moment," Pines said on Israel Radio.
</P>
<P>
He said he did not believe Barak's leaving is a negotiation
maneuver, adding that according to his sources, the American
sponsors shared with Barak the judgement that the Palestinians
adopted too tough stands in the talks.
</P>
<P>
Barak's leaving will indicate the break-off of the summit, which
began eight days ago at Camp David aiming to resolve all the
core issues between the two sides, such as the fate of Jerusalem,
Palestinian refugees, Jewish settlements, border, security and
water. 
</P>
</TEXT>
