or 1.46 percent higher at 2137.21 points, off from an intra-day
high of 2147.07 points.
</P>
<P>
The total volume increased to 575.48 million units worth 691.05
million Singapore dollars (about 397.16 million U.S. dollars).
Gainers led losers by 177 to 129 with 245 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
ITech Grp topped the volume list with a turnover of 84.00
million units. It was followed by Jadason which had 42.23 million
units done. FoodEmpire was the next with 26.95 million counters
changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Creative 50 led gainers of the day climbing up 150 cents to
close at 39.90 Singapore dollars. PacCent gained 140 cents to
finish at 24.80 Singapore dollars. Venture picked up 130 cents to
end at 20.80 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Global Tech led the losers list with a marginal drop of 16
cents closing at 2.10 Singapore dollars. Sp Land fell 12 cents to
finish at 3.46 Singapore dollars. Nat Broad retreated 9 cents to
end at 2.41 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said SingTel's announcement to build a pan-Asian
submarine cable system pushed up its share price, contributing
almost 12 points to the STI index.
</P>
<P>
They said banking and electronics stocks also ended higher
ahead of expectations for robust trade data due to be released by
the Trade Development Board on Thursday.  
</P>
