<HEADLINE> Malaysian Parties Sign Joint Venture Accord with Japan's Honda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Two Malaysian companies
Wednesday signed a memorandum of agreement (MoA) with Honda Motor
Co. Ltd. of Japan to manufacture and distribute Honda automobiles,
spare parts, accessories and components.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia's DRB-HICOM Bhd and Oriental Holdings Bhd will hold 36
percent in the joint venture, Oriental 15 percent and Honda 49
percent under the MoA signed in Putrajaya near here.
</P>
<P>
The parties will form a new entity, DRB-Oriental-Honda Sdn Bhd,
which will be incorporated beginning next year with an authorized
capital of 500 million ringgit (130 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
This joint venture is seen as a major boost to Malaysia's
automotive industry and also seen in line with Honda's regional
strategy of increasing its competitiveness in Malaysia and ASEAN
to meet the challenges of market liberalization under the ASEAN
Free Trade Area.
</P>
<P>
The signing ceremony was witnessed by Malaysian Prime Minister
Mahathir Mohamad. 
</P>
