<HEADLINE> Kenya to Introduce AIDS Curriculum in Schools </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 19 (Xinhua) -- The Kenyan government will
introduce a HIV/AIDS curriculum in both primary and secondary
schools by September this year, the People daily reported
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Permanent Secretary in the Education Ministry Japheth Kiptoon
said here Tuesday that the directors in his ministry are working
on modalities of retraining teachers to make them well acquainted
with the curriculum.
</P>
<P>
Kiptoon said emphasis will be laid on the preventive measures
and change of attitude towards the scourge which has so far seen
over 33.4 million people infected with the disease and over 16
million others dead in the world.
</P>
<P>
AIDS is rampant in Kenya since the first case was recorded in
1984 with some two million Kenyans having been infected by the
killer disease. 
</P>
</TEXT>
