<HEADLINE> Soeharto's Assets to be Seized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's Attorney General
Office (AGO) has decided to seize assets of former president
Soeharto on Thursday, Antara news agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
It said that the AGO will seize the "Granadi Building", one of
Soeharto's assets which is located in Kuningan District, South
Jakarta.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman of the AGO Yushar Yahya confirmed the planned move,
saying that the seizure of "Granadi Building" is a follow up made
by the AGO in settling the corruption cases which allegedly were
committed by Soeharto during his 32 years in power.
</P>
<P>
It seems that the seizure will be the first move made by the
AGO against the former strong man in its bid to bring the 79-year
old man to court.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, the South Jakarta District Court has endorsed seizure
by the AGO of the assets belonging to seven charity foundations
set up and chaired by Soeharto.
</P>
<P>
Soeharto is suspected of abusing of power and authority during
his 32-years in power. He has been put under house arrest and has
undergone several investigations by prosecutors from the AGO.
</P>
<P>
He is expected to appear before the court before August 10.
</P>
</TEXT>
