<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Fuel Oil Supply Reaches Alarming Level </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's fuel oil supply has
reached an alarming level as the present supplies are only enough
for 18 days instead of 23 days, while the government seems to
allow import premium oil to help neutralize the fuel shortage in
the domestic market, an official said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Marketing Manager of the state-owned oil and gas company
Pertamina, Harry Purnomo said that the shortage of fuel oil is due
to the damage in the country's Balongan oil refinery in West Java
province, adding that the refinery will begin normal operations by
July 26.
</P>
<P>
"The Pertamina has been facing difficulties in seeking oil
supplies from abroad as it has to compete with other buyers,
especially those from the U.S. west coast," Purnomo said, adding
that the company is thus trying to seek fuel oil from Malaysia,
Singapore and China.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Minister of Mines and Energy Susilo Bambang Yudhoyono
said that the government will import premium oil to help
neutralize the fuel shortage.
</P>
<P>
"I have issued an instruction for the import of premium oil if
domestic supplies are still running short," Yudhoyono said.
</P>
<P>
But he cautioned that the need to meet the people's demand and
not profit should be taken into account in importing the premium
oil, citing that Singapore could not supply Indonesia with premium
oil.
</P>
<P>
"The neighboring countries used to supply us during the time of
crisis at home. But it has run out of stock as it has shipped its
stock to American western and eastern coastal countries," he said,
adding that Kuwait also could not be expected to supply as the
country's main oil refinery has recently caught fire.
</P>
<P>
In another development, East Java and Bali provinces have been
running short of oil supplies over the past few days. Some gas
stations have run dry, while others have limited their sales to 10
liters per customer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
