<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Capital Goods Imports Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia's capital goods imports
during January-April this year reached 1.21 billion U.S. dollars,
or an increase of 6.41 percent against the same period last year,
according to data issued Wednesday by the Central Bureau of
Statistics (BPS).
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the bureau also recorded an increase in import for
raw materials by 20.94 percent to 7.02 billion U.S. dollars in the
first four months of this year.
</P>
<P>
"The increase of import for capital goods and raw materials
during that period showed that the production activities in the
country have begun to recover," the bureau said.
</P>
<P>
The bureau also disclosed that import for consumption goods
during January-April this year only reached 650.8 million U.S.
dollars or down 11.42 percent compared to the same period last
year which reached 734.7 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
"The decline of import for consumption goods was mainly due to
the descent in the import of food and drinks processed for
households by 58.83 percent to 194.5 million U.S. dollars from 472.
4 million U.S. dollars previously," the bureau said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
