<HEADLINE> South Korean Media Delegation to Visit Pyongyang Next Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, July 19 (Xinhua) -- A delegation of 50 heads of South
Korean major news media will visit the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea (DPRK) next month to activate press exchanges
and discuss cooperation measures.
</P>
<P>
In a news conference here Wednesday, Culture and Tourism
Minister Park Jie-won said that the heads of newspapers and
broadcasting companies will travel to the DPRK via Beijing.
</P>
<P>
