<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Belgium to Launch Campaign on Trade in Human Beings </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 19 (Xinhua) -- The Belgian government is
planning a campaign in newspapers of some foreign countries to
voice its determination to fight against the trafficking in human
beings, local media said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Believing that Chechen traffickers have been operating in human
beings in Central Asia, bringing illegal immigrants through
Ukraine to Western countries, including Belgium, the federal
government will put advertisements on newspapers in a number of
former Soviet republics in Central Asia, said the report.
</P>
<P>
Through the advertisements, Belgium is expected to convey a
message to those who want to come to Western countries for new
opportunities that Belgium is not a land of plenty where a bright
future is waiting, the report noted.
</P>
<P>
The Belgian government also has a plan to send officials to
those countries to cooperate with the local authorities to fight
against the trafficking of human beings.
</P>
<P>
Currently, Belgium is negotiating "return home" deals with
several countries in order to send illegals back to their home
more easily. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
