<HEADLINE> Guangzhou to Host International Stamp, Coin Exposition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 19 (Xinhua) -- A four-day international stamp and
coin exposition will be held on October 31 in Guangzhou, capital
of south China's Guangdong province.
</P>
<P>
It is the third time for China to host such a fair, which will
attract more than 100 post and coin-producing administrations and
businessmen from dozens of foreign countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
The first two were held in Beijing and Shanghai, respectively
in 1995 and 1997.
</P>
<P>
To commemorate the exposition, the People's Bank of China will
issue a silver coin with the portrait of panda, and the State Post
Administration will also issue a new stamp. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
