<HEADLINE> Flood Threatens Cambodia's Rice Farming </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, July 19(Xinhua)--At least nine provinces are facing
threat by flooding over the last few days where some hundred
hectares of rice farms are reportedly destroyed, said government
officials.
</P>
<P>
The flooding was caused by heavy rains coming from a storm
blowing in from the Indian Ocean after passing over parts of
Thailand, Laos and Vietnam, said the official at the Ministry of
Meteorology and Water Resource.
</P>
<P>
The flooding has touched parts of Takeo, Kampot, Kompong speu,
Kandal,Kampong Cham, Kratie, Siemreap, Udor Meanchey and Koh Kong.
</P>
<P>
Uy Sam Ath, director of disaster management for the Cambodia
Red Cross said food and other relief aid would be needed by
thousands of families.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Hun Sen has recently appealed to concerned
government's bodies to be alert on the flooding and take immediate
action in helping families or villagers from any possible disaster
including the threat to their lives.
</P>
<P>
The experts on water resource and meteorology have speculated
that water level would rise much higher than previous years.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
