<HEADLINE> 547 East Timorese Refugees Die in Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 19 (Xinhua) -- As many as 547 East Timorese
refugees have died due to several reasons in their camps in
Indonesia's East Nusa Tenggara Province from September 1999 until
May 2000, a report reaching here said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"Data collected by local officials showed that 547 East
Timorese refugees have died, until second week of May this year,"
Antara news agency quoted Governor of East Nusa Tenggara province,
Piet A Tallo as saying.
</P>
<P>
"But through a joint cooperation with the UNHCR ( United
Nations High Commissioner for Refugees), we have succeeded in
repatriating some 103,201 East Timorese refugees," Tallo added.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of local health office, Agus Berek confirmed the
figure of the death, adding that the refugees died mostly due to
malaria and respiratory disease.
</P>
<P>
"But several refugees died due to flood disaster in May in Belu
regency and for other accidents," he said.
</P>
<P>
Berek said that there are still 134,155 East Timorese refugees
in East Nusa Tenggara province.
</P>
<P>
East Timor is a former Indonesia's province. It separated from
Indonesia through a U.N.-sponsored direct ballot on August last
year, after a 23-years integration with Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
At least 284,000 East Timorese have fled to the neighboring
provinces to take shelter after the territory voted in favor of
independence which was then followed by mass riots involving pro-
integration and pro-independence groups. Hundreds of civilians
died during the riot which took place last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
