<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Number of South Korean Internet Banking Users Rising </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Some 1.23 million people used
Internet banking as of late June, with an average of 10,000
clients signing up to use the system a day, said the Bank of Korea
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Up to last March, 470,000 South Koreans registered to use the
Internet banking system.
</P>
<P>
South Korean clients used Internet banking 12.52 million times
to check their accounts, transfer money and take out loans in June,
up 159 percent from March.
</P>
<P>
Customers transferred funds 2.5 million times, exchanging 18.24
trillion won (about 16.4 billion U.S. dollars) all together.
</P>
<P>
They also took out 718.8 billion won (about 645.5 million
dollars) in loans through 83,000 log-ins.
</P>
<P>
All 20 South Korean domestic banks provide Internet banking
services except Korea Development and the Export and Import Bank.
</P>
<P>
The banks also provide mobile banking services, in which
clients can check accounts and transfer money using wireless
communication equipment.
</P>
<P>
The banks will expand their cyber operations by signing
partnerships with brokerage houses as more and more stock
investors use the Internet for trading. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
