<HEADLINE> More Shandong Enterprises to Open E-business </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Some 100,000 enterprises, or one-
fourth of the total in east China's Shandong province, will open
e-business via Internet by the end of this year, according to a
local senior official.
</P>
<P>
Some 80 percent of Shandong's enterprises will do online
business in the next three years, said Lin Shuxiang, vice governor
of the Province.
</P>
<P>
Statistics from Shandong telecom sector showed that only 4,000
enterprises have opened their own websites.
</P>
<P>
With the establishment of a wide-band and high-speed fiber
communication network, Shandong's exchange capacity has totaled
12 million lines, ranking the third in the country.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the province's comprehensive public e-business
system has also attracted over 400,000 Internet users. 
</P>
