<HEADLINE> Chuan: Thailand Firmly Sticks to "One China" Principle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Thai Prime Minister Chuan Leekpai
on Wednesday reiterated here that Thailand will firmly stick to
the "One China" Principle.
</P>
<P>
He made this remarks during the meeting with visiting Chinese
Vice-president Hu Jintao in the government house.
</P>
<P>
Hu pointed out that the Chinese government never changed its
basic policy of " Peaceful Unification and One Country, Two
Systems" on Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that the Thai government will continue sticking to the
'One China' Principle, " Hu said.
</P>
<P>
Chuan responded that the Thai government will always stick to
the "One China" Principle, and promised that Thailand will never
try to establish any official ties with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Wednesday, Chavalit Yongchaiyudh, former Thai prime
minister and leader of the opposition New Aspiration Party, and
Banharn Slipa-archa, another former premier and leader of the
opposition Chart Thai Party, also expressed their firm support to
the "One China" Principle during their separate meetings with the
Chinese Vice-president.
</P>
<P>
Both of the two former premiers said that their parties will
stick to the "One China" Principle and hope the unification of
China will be realized soon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
