<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0500 GMT, July 19 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA -- Zambian Finance Minister Katele Kalumba on Tuesday
unveiled his country's medium-term economic program, saying its
macroeconomic objectives for 2000-2002 are to achieve sustained
economic growth of 4-7 percent annually and further reduce
inflation to 11.5 percent in 2002 from the current about 25
percent. (Zambia-Economic-Program)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SAN JOSE -- The surge of oil prices has affected all Central
American countries, specially El Salvador, which registered
greatest gasoline increases, said the Secretariat of Central
American Economic Integration (SIECA) Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Super gasoline went up in the last three-month period a little
over 20 percent and Regular rose 10 percent in El Salvador, the
SIECA said in a report made known Tuesday by Costa Rica Petroleum
Refinery. (C.America-Oil Prices)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
