<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Polish Premier Jerzy Buzek Tuesday
named Senator Edmund Wittbrodt new education minister after the
resignation of Miroslaw Handke over a miscalculation of the
ministry's annual budget.
</P>
<P>
Handke, who served as education minister since late 1997,
tendered his resignation Monday after the education ministry
miscalculated an appropriation fund, causing a 800 million zloty (
200 million U.S. dollars) gap in the ministry's budget.
</P>
<P>
The funds in question were to cover a pay hike promised to
Poland's poorly paid teachers.
</P>
<P>
Wittbrodt, 53, who has an extensive background in education,
said he would continue the policy of reform initiated by Handke.
