<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yugoslavs Rebuilding Homeland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, July 18 (Xinhua) -- The Yugoslav people have made
great progress in rebuilding their homeland after NATO ended its
air strikes against the nation one year ago, said a report from
the Yugoslav general headquarters of rebuilding homeland on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
By July 11 this year, they repaired or rebuilt 41 highway
bridges, 15 railway bridges, 1 freeway and 8 highways, all
destroyed by the NATO bombing, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Another 837 residences, 4 thermal power plants, 10 schools, 6
hospitals, 2 farms and 17 public buildings were reconstructed. Now
builders are working at 67 construction sites, it said.
</P>
<P>
Instructed by President Slobodan Milosevic, the general
headquarters is carrying out a strategic program to build 100,000
sets of residence in the first decade of the 21 century, among
which, 10,000 sets will be put up in 2000, the report said.
</P>
<P>
To achieve the goal of the year, construction work has started
in 96 cities around the country, it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000719.0279 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-07-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Oil Prices Rebound after New OPEC Decision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Crude Prices on major world markets
bounced back Tuesday after the Organization of Petroleum Exporting
Countries decided to shelf the plan of increasing oil production.
</P>
<P>
OPEC President Ali Rodriquez announced a new decision in
Caracas Tuesday to hold back the OPEC plan of putting extra 500,
000 barrels of oil per day on the market, which was announced just
one day ago.
</P>
<P>
Immediately after the announcement, the crude price for August
delivery on the New York Mercantile Exchange soared 1.37 U.S.
dollars to 33.20 dollars a barrel. Meanwhile, the oil price for
September delivery on the London market also jumped 1.19 dollars
to 29.75 dollars.
</P>
<P>
Quite differently, oil prices went down Monday when the Vienna-
based OPEC Secretariat released a statement on a possible increase
of oil production. The statement says that the OPEC countries
would produce additional 500,000 barrels a day if the OPEC oil
price remains higher than 28 dollars a barrel by July 28.
</P>
<P>
In response, the price of the so-called OPEC basket of seven
different crudes fell 1.38 dollars to 27.46 dollars a barrel from
last Friday's 28.84 dollars.
</P>
<P>
OPEC believes a price between 22-28 dollars a barrel as a
desirable and sustainable price for the market. Therefore, it
decided last March to fluctuate its production along with the
movement of the price band.
</P>
<P>
The oil price had been hanging continuously above 28 dollars a
barrel for 19 trading days from June 20 to last Friday, which
became a serious concern of the world market as well as of the
OPEC. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
