<HEADLINE> Uruguay Came From Behind to Beat Venezuela Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Uruguay survived from a 1-0
down to beat Venezuela 3-1 on Tuesday in a dramatic and bad-
tempered World Cup qualifier which saw two players sent off.
</P>
<P>
Venezuela, who have lost every away World Cup qualifier since
1965, stunned the two-time former world champions by taking a 23rd-
minute lead through Daniel Noriega.
</P>
<P>
Uruguay hit back seven minutes later with a goal by Spanish-
based striker Nicolas Olivera. A header by defender Dario
Rodriguez in the 53rd minute and a second goal by Olivera in
injury time lift Uruguay to a victory.
</P>
<P>
The win gave Uruguay 10 points from five games in the South
American World Cup group and left Venezuela with four.
</P>
<P>
Uruguay striker Dario Silva was sent off midway through the
second half for a horrible late challenge on Leopoldo Jimenez, who
was also dismissed for retaliation.
</P>
<P>
The home side wasted an chance to go 1-0 ahead early in the game
when Alvaro Recoba missed a penalty.
</P>
<P>
The Venezuelans silenced the 62,000 spectators when Gabriel
Urdaneta sent a bouncing ball into the Uruguay penalty and
Noriega slipped between three defenders to poke the ball into the
net.
</P>
<P>
Trailing 1-0 behind, Uruguay found their rhythm soon and put
the Venezuela goalkeeper under intense pressure.
</P>
<P>
They made it 1-all in the 30th minute with a goal from Gianni
Guigou in the penalty area, where Olivera controlled it on his
chest and then volleyed into the goal on the turn. 
</P>
</TEXT>
