<HEADLINE> China's Central Bank Increases Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 19 (Xinhua) -- The People's Bank of China, the
central bank, increased its loans by 150 billion yuan during the
first six months this year.
</P>
<P>
The increased loans were thus 200 billion yuan larger than in
the corresponding period of last year, said Dai Xianglong,
governor of the People's Bank of China, at the press conference
held here today.
</P>
<P>
He said that since the beginning of this year, the People's
Bank of China has given further play to the role of monetary
policy in facilitating economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The acceleration of the financial reform, the improvement in
the credit structure, the strengthening of financial supervision
and the reduction in the non-performing loans have all contributed
to the positive financial performance and conspicuously promoted
the national economic growth, the governor said. 
</P>
