<HEADLINE> Exchange of Officials Helps Improve Efficiency </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 19 (Xinhua) -- The exchanges of officials at both
the central and local levels have helped improve government work
efficiency and raise the quality of Party and government
functionaries.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years, a total of 175,000 Party and
government officials at or above the county level have been
transferred from their hometowns to other posts elsewhere,
according to a People's Daily report today.
</P>
<P>
Of the total 175,000, some 400 are Party and government
officials at the ministerial or provincial level. The central
authorities have viewed the exchange of officials as part of the
efforts to strengthen the building up of the cadre contingent and
an effective way in reforming the personnel system.
</P>
<P>
The exchanges have proven conducive to the building of a clean
and honest government at all levels while providing more chances
for young cadres to give free reins to their talents, the report
says. 
</P>
