<HEADLINE> Moderate Earthquake Hits Northern Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 19 (Xinhua) -- An earthquake measuring 5.5 on the
Richter scale jolted the northwest Philippine province of Ilocos
Norte early Wednesday morning, the Philippine Institute of
Volcanology and Seismology (Phivolcs) said.
</P>
<P>
The Philvocs said in a report that the tremor, which is of
tectonic origin, rocked the province at around 6:59 a.m. local
time. No damage was reported.
</P>
<P>
The epicenter of the quake was traced at 39 kilometers
southwest of Laoag, the provincial capital city.
</P>
<P>
A Phivolcs representative said the quake was triggered by the
movement of the Manila trench.
</P>
<P>
The same representative, however, clarified that the movement
is not related to the powerful quake which hit the northernmost
province of Batanes last Sunday, which measured 6.4 on the Richter
scale. 
</P>
