Political Consultative Conference, met with visiting Russian
President Vladimir Putin respectively. Chinese leaders and Putin
exchanged views on enhancing the political, trade and economic
cooperation between China and Russia.
</P>
<P>
 China Daily
</P>
<P>
-- China's Vice Premier Qian Qichen met Tuesday with a 26-
member delegation from Taiwan's Kuomintang party.
</P>
<P>
Qian told the Taiwan visitors that the Taiwan authorities'
evasion of the One-China Principle is the fundamental factor that
has made the resumption of cross-Straits talks and improvement of
the ties difficult.
</P>
