<HEADLINE> Foot injury forces O'Brien out of US Olympic Trials </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Dan O'Brien's hope to defending
his Olympic decathlon title was demolished when a foot injury
suffered in training forced him out of the US Trials in Sacramento
of California.
</P>
<P>
O'Brien said Tuesday that he had torn the plantar fascia -- a
band of connective tissue between the heel and the toes -- in his
left foot last week and could not compete.
</P>
<P>
It's the second Olympian disappointment for O'Brien, who was
expected to contend for a medal in 1992, but failed to qualify
when he failed to post a height in the decathlon pole vault at the
US trials. 
</P>
