<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazilian Sprinter Parrela Tests Positive for Drug </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Men's 400 meters world
silver medallist Sanderlei Parrela of Brazil has been tested
positive for drug, the Brazilian Athletics Confederation (CBaT)
said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Parrela tested positive for the banned steroid norandrosterone,
following the Rio de Janeiro Grand Prix meeting on May 14, said a
statement signed by CBaT general secretary Martinho Nobre dos
Santos.
</P>
<P>
The statement said the CBaT had been told by the International
Amateur Athletic Federation that both the A and B samples,
examined by a laboratory in Montreal, had tested positive for the
substance.
</P>
<P>
The 25-year-old sprinter has been automatically banned pending
a final hearing. If the hearing confirms the test findings, he
could be banned for two years and would miss the Sydney Olympics
starting in September. 
</P>
</TEXT>
