<HEADLINE> Virenque Scores First Stage Win in Three Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Frenchman Richard Virenque won the
final Alpine stage to for his first Tour de France stage win for
three years on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
He finished the 196.5 kms stage from Courchevel to Morzine 24
seconds clear of German Jan Ullrich, whose second place cut the
overall lead of Lance Armstrong to five minutes 37 seconds.
</P>
<P>
The American finished two minutes one second behind Virenque.
</P>
</TEXT>
