<HEADLINE> Swede Alexandersson Sets to Join Everton </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 18 (Xinhua) -- Swedish international Niclas
Alexandersson is set to join English premier league Everton from
relegated Sheffield Wednesday for 2.5 million pounds (3.74 million
US dollars), the clubs said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The winger, who is waiting for the results of a medical, has
agreed personal terms with Everton on a four-year contract.
</P>
<P>
Wednesday were relegated to the first division last year.
</P>
<P>
Everton entered the transfer market to replace midfielders Nick
Barmby, Don Hutchison and John Collins who left to join Liverpool,
Sunderland and Fulham respectively. 
</P>
