<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fish Prices Drop Sharply in Rwanda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Fish prices in Rwanda have gone
down by 61.5 percent since the ban on fishing products from East
African countries was lifted in May this year, the Rwanda News
Agency quoted an agricultural official as saying on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
According to the Ministry of Agriculture, the lift has boosted
the country's economy because the tax base has widened due to an
increase in fish importers.
</P>
<P>
Customers, on the other hand, have had low prices at the local
market due to increased supply.
</P>
<P>
Rwanda imposed a ban on fish from Uganda in March last year
following reports that fishermen used poison in fishing on Lake
Victoria, shared by the three East African countries -- Uganda,
Kenya and Tanzania. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
