<HEADLINE> Pardon of Prisoners Welcomed in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 20 (Xinhua) -- The Uganda Human Rights Commission
(UHRC) has welcomed the recent presidential pardon of 522
prisoners from prisons countrywide and the commuting of death
sentences of 16 others to life imprisonment.
</P>
<P>
The act of President Yoweri Museveni and the government will
ease the serious overcrowding in the prisons, reduce the costs of
maintaining prisoners and ultimately lead to improved living
conditions of the inmates, Radio Uganda said here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The UHRC has for the past three years advocated for better
living conditions for all prisoners, especially for the pregnant
women, the terminally ill and the aged who are already too weak to
endure the difficult prison conditions, the radio said. 
</P>
