<HEADLINE> Angolan Warring Parties Urged to Honor Humanitarian Conventions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Warring parties in Angola should
keep their commitments in the peace protocol and honor
international humanitarian conventions, an International Red Cross
official said here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"International humanitarian law does not have the mechanisms to
end conflicts, but their application can permit the creation of
areas of respect among the parties in conflict, beyond avoiding
inhuman acts which generate hate and rancor and the destruction of
infrastructures", Francaise Zamberlini told a peace congress
sponsored by social settlements in Luanda.
</P>
<P>
Zamberlini urged both sides to allow access by aid groups to
populations victimized by the war.
</P>
<P>
The Peace Congress starting from Tuesday is scheduled to run
through July 21. It is aimed at helping the Angolan government and
the rebel movement led by Jonas Savimbi "find the pathways to
peace". 
