<HEADLINE> Kenya Attracts 900,000 Visitors Last Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Kenya attracted 900,000 foreign
visitors last year with its unique national parks and good hotels,
the East African Standard newspaper reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"Kenya is not losing tourists to Central Africa because we are
not faced with the kind of land crisis currently facing Zimbabwe,"
Tourism, Trade and Industry Minister Nicholas Biwott was quoted as
saying here on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
An estimated 1 million tourists will have visited Kenya by the
end of this year, he said during the inauguration of the board of
Kenya Tourist Development Corporation.
</P>
<P>
According to the minister, a total of 240 million shillings (
about 3.1 million U.S. dollars) has been set aside for the
promotion of tourist-related activities and the income from
tourism is expected to grow by 25 percent this year.
</P>
<P>
The ministry has introduced the concept of mountain climbing,
sports and cultural entertainment to allure more visitors, Biwott
said, noting that the government would invest heavily towards
rehabilitation of the country's infrastructure, especially in
tourism.
</P>
<P>
He urged Kenyans to change their attitude and speak well of
their country abroad, noting that the country has some of the best
tourist facilities in the world.
</P>
<P>
Tourism is the third foreign currency earner after coffee and
tea for Kenya. Wild animals like elephants, leopards and
hippopotamus have made the country a popular destination in Africa.
</P>
</TEXT>
