<HEADLINE> Stable Oil Prices To Benefit OPEC: Venezuelan President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Venezuelan President Hugo Chavez
said Wednesday that the process of stabilizing crude prices will
strengthen the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries (OPEC)
.
</P>
<P>
Chavez made this statement after receiving OPEC General
Secretary Rilwanu Lukman Wednesday afternoon in the Miraflores
Palace.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was held at the Miraflores Palace Hall of the
Mirrors, where Chavez and Lukman discussed important topics as
well as the details related to the preparations for the Summit of
OPEC Dignitaries, crude prices, and the market situation.
</P>
<P>
Lukman gave a press conference at which he explained that the
OPEC is and will be a respectable organization, whose purpose is
to stabilize the market to keep it open to the law of supply and
demand, originated in the competition for the oil prices.
</P>
<P>
He said that there are people who want to speculate with the
situation, and that this is not the goal of the organization, and
that what is desired is to stabilize the market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
