<HEADLINE> Mexico Records Trade Surplus with U.S. in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Mexico recorded an
unprecedented trade surplus with the United States of 2.089
billion dollars in May, the U.S. Department of Commerce said
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The surplus resulted from Mexico's record exports to the United
States for 11 billion dollars that surpassed the imports for 8.911
billion dollars from that country, according to reports from
Washington.
</P>
<P>
The May trade surplus of Mexico with the United States was 40.
89 percent higher than the 2.453 billion dollars of April.
</P>
<P>
Mexico keeps being the second U.S. commercial partner after
Canada. The three countries implemented in January of 1994 the
North America Free Trade Agreement.
</P>
<P>
The United States is Mexico's first trade partner, and 80
percent of its trade is made with that country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
