<HEADLINE> Addis Ababa Recommended as Capital of African Union: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia has expressed its
hope to have Addis Ababa as the capital of a future African Union,
similar to the European Union, local Press Digest reported
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopian Prime Minister Meles Zenawi raised the issue at the
end of the 36th summit of the Organization of African Unity (OAU)
held in Lome, Togo not long ago, the weekly said.
</P>
<P>
Presently, OAU's headquarters is in Addis Ababa, capital of
Ethiopia, which is also home to the United Nations Economic
Commission for Africa, and the African offices of the
International Francophone Organization.
</P>
<P>
OAU spokesman Desmond Orjiako said last week that all African
countries had accepted the idea of establishing the African Union.
However, the act of the African Union would have to be ratified by
the parliaments of at least two-thirds of the 53 member states of
the OAU.
</P>
<P>
It was predicted that ratification of such a text could lead to
the disappearance of the OAU within one year.
</P>
<P>
The OAU, the biggest political organization in Africa, was
established in May 1963. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
